I only started watching #GameofThrones a month ago. It's very good. But more importantly, I don't think I've ever seen a pop culture phenomenon like it. 

It is *everywhere*.
There isn't one publication or news source I read that doesn't have some kind of GoT coverage. It is absolutely insane.

I haven't been consumed by it because I haven't watched it as it was intended to be watched. But it's very, very good, and if you haven't given it a try, you should, not least because whether you like it or not, it's this generation's Star Wars, and maybe more.
I can't remember seeing anything that has permeated through every fabric of daily life like it.
I can’t do this anymore

Along with Marvel, GoT represents a golden age of popular fiction that can't and shouldn't be ignored. 

Savour it, enjoy it, go along with it. It might not ever get better than this.
